  array (
    'name' => 'system_profiler',
    'description' => 'Retrieve detailed system information using PHP\'s FFI (Foreign Function Interface). Calls native C library and OS API functions that no other PHP tool can reach. Returns: OS info, system uptime (ms), CPU count, architecture, page size, process ID, process CPU time, system memory stats (total/available/free), and clock resolution. Uses FFI to dynamically load msvcrt.dll/kernel32.dll on Windows or libc on Unix and call functions like GetTickCount64, GetSystemInfo, GlobalMemoryStatusEx, clock, and sysconf. First FFI-based tool in the ecosystem — opens up native system-level capabilities no PHP function provides. Never throws — all errors returned as structured data.',
